0US%20service%20member%20points%20a%20handheld%20device%20at%20a%20drone%20at%20the%20JCU%20in%20October%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EAmber%20Osei%2FUS%20Army%20Air%20Defense%20Artillery%20School%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELt.%20Col.%20Moseph%20Sauda%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20JCU%2C%20doesn't%20believe%20the%20US%20is%20lagging%20behind%20with%20its%20counter-drone%20training.%20%26quot%3BThe%20issue%20is%20you%20could%20be%20so%20successful%20that%20you%20fail%20to%20continue%20to%20develop%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI%20during%20a%20visit%20to%20Fort%20Sill%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20emphasizing%20the%20importance%20of%20remaining%20agile%20and%20flexible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20future%20of%20warfare%2C%20if%20we%20had%20to%20fight%20and%20win%20today%20in%20this%20current%20environment%20with%20what's%20going%20on%20in%20flying%2C%20we%20would%20still%20win%2C%26quot%3B%20Sauda%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20enemy%20is%20still%20going%20to%20evolve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20comes%20next%2C%20such%20as%20autonomous%20swarms%20or%20some%20other%20threat%2C%20likely%20at%20a%20scale%20not%20previously%20seen%2C%20could%20be%20vastly%20more%20daunting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20US%20isn't%20yet%20ready%20to%20face%20drones%20in%20combat%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica's%20next%20war%20may%20not%20look%20exactly%20like%20Ukraine%20and%20instead%20be%20a%20unique%20horror.%20Conflict%20with%20China%2C%20which%20some%20officials%20have%20warned%20is%20possible%2C%20would%20likely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-not-ready-china-war-military-economy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunfold%20predominantly%20across%20a%20vast%20maritime%20domain%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20unmanned%20systems%2C%20including%20small%20drones%2C%20could%20be%20a%20factor%2C%20nonetheless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20military%20recognizes%20this%20and%20is%20now%20looking%20at%20building%20out%20its%20own%20drone%20force.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20unveiled%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FNews-Stories%2FArticle%2FArticle%2F3657609%2Fdefense-innovation-official-says-replicator-initiative-remains-on-track%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Replicator%20initiative%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20monthslong%20plan%20to%20field%20thousands%20of%20autonomous%20systems%20to%20counter%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20drone%20pilot%20reaches%20for%20a%20reconnaissance%20drone%20in%20the%20Luhansk%20Region%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20Saturday%2C%20Aug.%2019%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6511967059fd710019eff726%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20drone%20pilot%20reaches%20for%20a%20reconnaissance%20drone%20in%20the%20Luhansk%20Region%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20Saturday%2C%20Aug.%2019%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FBram%20Janssen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20military%20could%20also%20face%20this%20kind%20of%20threat%20in%20a%20war%20with%20Russia%20in%20Europe%2C%20a%20possibility%20should%20Russia%20emerge%20victorious%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20or%20in%20a%20conflict%20with%20Iran%2C%20which%20regularly%20engages%20in%20malign%20activity%2C%20such%20as%20producing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firanian-suicide-kamikaze-drones-russia-uses-ukraine-cities-explainer-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone-way%20attack%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Russia%20and%20arming%20proxy%20forces%20throughout%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20US%20military%20is%20not%20as%20ready%20for%20a%20large-scale%20drone%20conflict%20%26quot%3Bas%20many%20people%20would%20like%20it%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Scharre%2C%20now%20the%20executive%20vice%20president%20and%20director%20of%20studies%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20a%20New%20American%20Security%20think%20tank%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drone%20threat%20draws%20certain%20parallels%20to%20fighting%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20where%20hidden%20bombs%20posed%20a%20tremendous%20threat.%20Even%20though%20Washington%20had%20options%20to%20counter%20the%20problem%2C%20insurgents%20often%20adapted%20and%20changed%20their%20tactics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImprovised%20explosive%20devices%20are%20well%20known%20threats%20that%2C%20over%20the%20years%2C%20have%20killed%20and%20maimed%20countless%20US%20service%20members.%20The%20danger%20is%20that%20exploding%20drones%2C%20the%20flying%20equivalent%2C%20are%20now%20similarly%20cheap%20and%20accessible%2C%20even%20for%20militant%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20US%20military%20has%20often%20struggled%20to%20counter%20these%20sort%20of%20cheap%20tools%20of%20harassment%20that%20are%20widely%20available%20to%20state%20and%20nonstate%20groups%20alike%2C%26quot%3B%20Scharre%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20might%20not%20stop%20the%20US%20military's%20ability%20to%20go%20into%20an%20area%2C%20but%20it%20can%20slow%20them%20down%20and%20cause%20casualties.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222694%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20soldiers%20are%20seen%20during%20an%20IED%20training%20course%20at%20the%20US%20Base%20at%20Bagram%20north%20of%20Kabul%2C%20Afghanistan%20on%20April%2029%2C%202009.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6639246e10dfcda409672f0f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221781%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20soldiers%20are%20seen%20during%20an%20IED%20training%20course%20at%20the%20US%20Base%20at%20Bagram%20north%20of%20Kabul%2C%20Afghanistan%20on%20April%2029%2C%202009.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FMusadeq%20Sadeq%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EScharre%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThese%20technologies%20kind%20of%20create%20this%20environment%20that%20I%20think%20is%20much%20more%20transparent%20and%20lethal%2C%20and%20is%20one%20that%20the%20US%20military%20hasn't%20really%20fully%20adapted%20to%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreparing%20for%20the%20drone%20fight%20is%20not%20just%20important%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20critical%2C%20Justin%20Bronk%20and%20Jack%20Watling%2C%20war%20experts%20and%20senior%20fellows%20at%20London's%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%20think%20tank%2C%20wrote%20last%20month%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Foccasional-papers%2Fmass-precision-strike-designing-uav-complexes-land-forces%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArmies%20that%20are%20unprepared%20to%20face%20this%20threat%20on%20the%20battlefield%20risk%20handing%20an%20enemy%20force%20highly%20valuable%20battlefield%20awareness%20and%20making%20themselves%20vulnerable%20to%20devastating%20precision%20strikes%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20appears%20to%20be%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20absorbing%20lessons%20from%20overseas%20and%20training%20its%20soldiers%20on%20how%20to%20prepare.%20But%20experts%20say%20the%20military%20still%20needs%20to%20significantly%20boost%20its%20procurement%20of%20counter-drone%20defenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECountering%20the%20drone%20threat%20means%20%26quot%3Bscaling%20up%20things%20like%20electronic%20warfare%20in%20a%20way%20that%20we%20just%20haven't%20done%20before%2C%20not%20even%20in%20the%20counter-IED%20battle%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryan%2C%20the%20retired%20Australian%20major%20general%2C%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BWe've%20kind%20of%20done%20it%2C%20but%20we%20need%20to%20do%20it%20at%20a%20whole%20new%20scale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20will%20also%20have%20to%20incorporate%20key%20systems%20into%20the%20training%20regimens%20of%20every%20unit%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20he%20said.%20And%20the%20US%20military%20will%20need%20far%20more%20drone-defense%20u