l%20Revanna%20is%20the%20grandson%20of%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Deve%20Gowda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20a%20Diplomatic%20Passport%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiplomatic%20passports%2C%20distinguishable%20by%20their%20maroon%20covers%2C%20differ%20from%20regular%20passports%20primarily%20in%20their%20privileges%20and%20immunities%20under%20international%20law.%20Issued%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%2C%20diplomatic%20passports%20are%20given%20to%20these%20individuals%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E-%20Diplomatic%20Status%3A%20Individuals%20with%20diplomatic%20status%20representing%20the%20government%20in%20official%20capacities.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn-%20Government%20Appointees%3A%20Those%20appointed%20by%20the%20government%20for%20official%20business%20abroad.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn-%20Senior%20Officers%3A%20Senior%20officers%20of%20the%20Indian%20Foreign%20Service%20(IFS)%20at%20Joint%20Secretary%20rank%20and%20above.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn-%20Family%20Members%3A%20Relatives%20and%20immediate%20family%20of%20IFS%20and%20MEA%20officers.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn-%20Selected%20Individuals%3A%20This%20category%20includes%20union%20ministers%20and%20MPs%20undertaking%20official%20government%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiplomatic%20passports%20are%20valid%20for%20five%20years%20or%20less%2C%20with%20validity%20often%20tied%20to%20the%20term%20of%20the%20holder's%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVisa%20Exemption%20Agreements%3A%20Prajwal%20Revanna's%20Case%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20ordinary%20citizens%20require%20visas%20for%20international%20travel%2C%20holders%20of%20diplomatic%20passports%20enjoy%20exemptions%20in%20certain%20countries.%20Prajwal%20Revanna's%20case%20has%20brought%20to%20light%20India's%20visa%20exemption%20agreement%20with%20Germany%2C%20established%20in%202011.%20This%20agreement%20allows%20Indian%20diplomatic%20passport%20holders%20to%20travel%20to%20Germany%20without%20a%20visa%20for%20up%20to%2090%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20despite%20the%20visa%20exemption%2C%20individuals%20with%20diplomatic%20passports%20are%20still%20required%20to%20obtain%20prior%20political%20clearance%20for%20private%20visits%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20Can%20Cancel%20A%20Diplomatic%20Passport%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnataka%20Chief%20Minister%20Siddaramaiah's%20call%20for%20the%20cancellation%20of%20Prajwal%20Revanna's%20diplomatic%20passport%20underscores%20the%20legal%20processes%20involved.%20According%20to%20the%20Passport%20Act%201967%2C%20the%20passport%20authority%20may%20revoke%20a%20diplomatic%20passport%20under%20specific%20circumstances%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWrongful%20Possession%3A%20If%20the%20passport%20is%20obtained%20through%20fraudulent%20means%20or%20if%20the%20holder%20is%20in%20wrongful%20possession.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENational%20Interests%3A%20Revocation%20can%20occur%20if%20it's%20deemed%20necessary%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20India's%20sovereignty%2C%20integrity%2C%20or%20friendly%20relations%20with%20other%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConviction%3A%20If%20the%20holder%20is%20convicted%20and%20sentenced%20to%20imprisonment%20for%20not%20less%20than%20two%20years%20after%20the%20passport's%20issuance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECourt%20Orders%3A%20Diplomatic%20passports%20can%20be%20revoked%20upon%20court%20orders%20during%20criminal%20proceedings%20against%20the%20holder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20crucial%20to%20note%20that%20diplomats%20enjoy%20certain%20immunities%2C%20including%20protection%20from%20arrest%20and%20prosecution%2C%20tax%20exemptions%2C%20and%20privileges%20regarding%20diplomatic%20premises%20and%20baggage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Karnataka%20government%20has%20issued%20a%20Blue%20Corner%20Notice%20against%20Prajwal%20Revanna%2C%20who%20is%20claimed%20to%20be%20in%20Germany%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Is%20A%20Blue-Corner%20Notice%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Blue%20Corner%20Notice%20is%20a%20part%20of%20Interpol's%20colour-coded%20notices%20that%20enable%20countries%20to%20share%20alerts%20and%20requests%20for%20information%20worldwide.%20They%20are%20international%20requests%20for%20cooperation%20or%20alerts%20allowing%20police%20in%20member%20countries%20to%20share%20critical%20crime-related%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20seven%20types%20of%20notices%20-%20Red%2C%20Yellow%2C%20Blue%2C%20Black%2C%20Green%2C%20Orange%2C%20and%20Purple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Blue%20notice%20is%20served%20to%20collect%20additional%20information%20about%20a%20person's%20identity%2C%20location%2C%20or%20activities%20in%20a%20criminal%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20the%20notice%20would%20help%20further%20the%20investigating%20agencies'%20inquiries%20against%20Prajwal%20Revanna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715404200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Flmmnkp3g_prajwal-revanna_625x300_27_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhow-prajwal-revanna-accused-of-sex-harassment-left-india-without-a-visa-5637878%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20sexual%20abuse%20case%20against%20Janata%20Dal%20(Secular)%20MP%20Prajwal%20Revanna%20has%20put%20the%20spotlight%20on%20diplomatic%20passports%20as%20the%20leader%20managed%20to%20leave%20India%20despite%20the%20investigation%20being%20on.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhow-prajwal-revanna-accused-of-sex-harassment-left-india-without-a-visa-5637878%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhow-prajwal-revanna-accused-of-sex-harassment-left-india-without-a-visa-5637878%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhow-prajwal-revanna-accused-of-sex-harassment-left-india-without-a-visa-5637878%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%