%20how%20it%20differs%20from%20OpenAI.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20smartphone%20displays%20the%20DeepMind%20logo%20in%20front%20of%20a%20blurred%20Google%20logo%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66155f2916bde8d4ead6eb2b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221303%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20DeepMind%20is%20Google's%20AI%20research%20division%20focused%20on%20building%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%2C%20also%20known%20as%20AGI.%3Cp%3EPavlo%20Gonchar%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDeepMind%20is%20Google's%20AI%20research%20hub%20focused%20on%20building%20artificial%20general%20intelligence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDeepMind%20has%20been%20applied%20to%20real-world%20problems%20in%20healthcare%2C%20science%2C%20and%20engineering.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDeepMind%20has%20a%20number%20of%20competitors%2C%20including%20OpenAI%2C%20though%20Google's%20model%20is%20for%20profit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20artificial%20intelligence%20has%20stepped%20out%20of%20the%20pages%20of%20science%20fiction%20and%20into%20everyday%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20we're%20surrounded%20by%20AI%20systems%20like%20Gemini%2C%20ChatGPT%2C%20Dall-E%2C%20CoPilot%2C%20and%20countless%20others%2C%20but%20Google%20DeepMind%20is%20somewhat%20different.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaunched%20back%20in%202010%2C%20DeepMind%20is%20a%20company%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20developing%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-agi-artificial-general-intelligence-explained-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eartificial%20general%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20AGI.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a5481cb-28b1-4e5b-8458-972c1c7df8ec%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20does%20Google's%20DeepMind%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20AI%20systems%20in%20use%20today%20are%20very%20good%20at%20completing%20specific%20kinds%20of%20tasks%20for%20which%20they%20were%20trained%2C%20the%20goal%20of%20AGI%20is%20to%20build%20a%20human-like%20intelligence%20that%20can%20learn%2C%20reason%2C%20and%20problem-solve%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20topics%20and%20tasks%20across%20a%20plethora%20of%20domains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20it's%20designed%20to%20mimic%20human%20intelligence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20different%20from%20systems%20like%20ChatGPT%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-gemini-firestorm-big-tech-ai-arms-race-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Gemini%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20are%20narrow%20AI%20systems%20that%20are%20very%20good%20at%20the%20specific%20task%20of%20understanding%20natural%20language%20well%20enough%20to%20deliver%20useful%20information%20through%20human-like%20interactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20DeepMind%20has%20not%20yet%20achieved%20AGI%2C%20but%20has%20made%20impressive%20achievements%20nonetheless.%20In%20practice%2C%20DeepMind%20has%20been%20applied%20to%20solving%20real-world%20problems%20in%20healthcare%2C%20science%20and%20engineering.%20It's%20perhaps%20most%20famous%2C%20though%2C%20for%20its%20mastery%20of%20enormously%20challenging%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20for%20example%2C%20DeepMind's%20AlphaGo%20became%20the%20first%20computer%20program%20to%20ever%20defeat%20a%20human%20opponent%20at%20Go%20(a%20game%20considered%20far%20more%20complex%20than%20chess).%20Less%20than%20two%20years%20later%2C%20AlphaGo%20went%20on%20to%20defeat%20the%20top-ranked%20Go%20player%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223074a853-5e90-49b8-bf5b-da0315a2ffe3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20runs%20Google's%20DeepMind%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Demis%20Hassabis%20wearing%20a%20suit%2C%20a%20red%20tie%2C%20and%20blue-framed%20glasses%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661507ec16bde8d4ead6cb99%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222192%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDemis%20Hassabis%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20Google%20DeepMind.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDeepMind%20was%20created%20in%202010%20by%20a%20trio%20of%20computer%20engineers%20from%20the%20Gatsby%20Computational%20Neuroscience%20Unit%20at%20University%20College%20London%2C%20and%20early%20research%20focused%20on%20getting%20AI%20systems%20to%20learn%20to%20play%20games%20without%20any%20instruction%20%E2%80%94%20the%20software%20would%20learn%20games%20like%20Breakout%2C%20Pong%20and%20Space%20Invaders%20through%20trial%20and%20error%2C%20eventually%20mastering%20the%20rules%20and%20becoming%20an%20expert%20at%20the%20games.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20acquired%20DeepMind%20in%202014%20for%20a%20price%20somewhere%20between%20%24400%20million%20and%20%24650%20million.%20Today%2C%20the%20company%20remains%20a%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-alphabet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20Alphabet%3C%2Fa%3E%20portfolio%20of%20businesses%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind-ceo-ai-too-hyped-in-some-senses-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDemis%20Hassabis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20of%20DeepMinds%20three%20original%20founders%2C%20continues%20to%20lead%20the%20development%20of%20AGI%20as%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalls-for-google-ceo-sundar-pichai-alphabet-step-down-ai-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%20Sundar%20Pichai%20announced%20that%20Google%20would%20merge%20DeepMind%20with%20the%20Brain%20team%20from%20Google%20Research%20to%20create%20a%20single%20AI%20unit%20%E2%80%94%20named%20Google%20DeepMind%20%E2%80%94%20to%20%26quot%3Bhelp%20us%20build%20more%20capable%20systems%20more%20safely%20and%20responsibly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20DeepMind%20remains%20based%20in%20London%20primarily%2C%20but%20also%20has%20researchers%20in%20Montreal%2C%20Canada%2C%20and%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogles-silicon-valley-office-space-inspired-by-salt-mine-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogleplex%3C%2Fa%3E%20corporate%20headquarters%20in%20Mountain%20View%2C%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b61290e-f5de-4dcc-9740-45917c875218%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20the%20difference%20between%20DeepMind%20and%20OpenAI%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20DeepMind%20is%20hardly%20alone%20in%20its%20AI%20research%20and%20development%3B%20it%20has%20a%20number%20of%20competitors%2C%20including%20the%20headline-making%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20two%20companies%20take%20a%20very%20different%20approach%20to%20AI%20development%2C%20though.%20DeepMind%20is%20a%20for-profit%20part%20of%20Google's%20Alphabet%2C%20Inc.%2C%20for%20example%2C%20while%20OpenAI%20was%20originally%20established%20as%20a%20non-profit%2C%20before%20transitioning%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-not-best-name-for-company-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bcapped-profit%26quot%3B%20model%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20companies%20have%20developed%20AI%20models%20and%20applications%20in%20ways%20that%20have%20contributed%20to%20AI%20research%20in%20sometimes%20complementary%20ways.%20While%20DeepMind%20mastered%20Go%20with%20AlphaGo%2C%20for%20example%2C%20OpenAI%20developed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gpt-3-language-generation-model-important-breakthrough-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGenerative%20Pre-trained%20Transformer%20language%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%20(for%20example%2C%20ChatGPT)%20that%20allow%20machines%20to%20better%20understand%20natural%20language%2C%20for%20more%20interactive%20and%20immersive%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222aca6bd3-b39c-4380-a9c4-0ec8f8633467%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20need%20a%20PhD%20to%20work%20at%20DeepMind%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20deep%20complexity%20of%20what%20DeepMind%20is%20developing%2C%20one%20might%20assume%20that%20prospective%20employees%20might%20all%20require%20a%20PhD.%20In%20reality%2C%20though%2C%20that's%20not%20true.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-job-resume-tips-machine-learning-specialist-career-switch-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20hires%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20large%20number%20of%20researchers%20and%20computer%20engineers%20with%20lesser%20degrees%20to%20help%20advance%20the%20state%20of%20the%20art%20in%20artificial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715384702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66155f671caec1275a6e2369%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Google%20DeepMind%20develops%20AI%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20making%20an%20artificial%20general%20intelligence.%20Here's%20what%20DeepMind%20does%20and%20how%20it%20differs%20from%20OpenAI.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Dave%20Johnson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A83%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Doctor%20Who%E2%80%99%20Star%20Jinkx%20Monsoon%20Unpacks%20Maestro%2C%20the%20Series%E2%80%99%20Wackiest%2C%20Most%20Musical%20Villain%20Yet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22publish