20they%20outnumber%20the%20amount%20of%20traditional%20rentals%20tagged%20for%20development%20over%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2050%25%20of%20total%20condos%20in%20the%20pre-construction%20phase%20across%20Miami-Dade%20County%20and%20nearby%20Broward%20County%2C%20totaling%2010%2C335%20units%2C%20are%20geared%20toward%20short-term%20rentals%2C%20a%20first-quarter%20report%20from%20real-estate%20firm%20ISG%20World%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20units%20may%20not%20be%20exclusively%20advertised%20for%20short-term%20stays%2C%20CEO%20of%20ISG%20World%20Craig%20Studnicky%20told%20Business%20Insider%20but%20were%20grouped%20by%20little%20to%20no%20rental%20restrictions%20for%20future%20owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20these%20units%20could%2C%20and%20very%20likely%20may%2C%20be%20used%20for%20Airbnb%20and%20similar%20purposes%2C%20Studnicky%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20had%20a%20development%20industry%20that%20is%20adding%20more%20short-term%20rentals%20to%20South%20Florida%20inventory%2C%26quot%3B%20Studnicky%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20not%20what%20we%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlorida%20has%20continued%20to%20experience%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-are-people-moving-florida-home-prices-cost-of-living-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20a%20major%20population%20boom%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20was%20the%20fastest-growing%20state%20between%202021%20and%202022%2C%20with%20417%2C000%20new%20residents.%20Housing%20prices%2C%20in%20tandem%2C%20skyrocketed.%20The%20median%20sales%20price%20for%20a%20home%20in%20Miami%20hit%20%24600%2C000%20in%20March%202024%2C%20nearly%20double%20the%20median%20price%20of%20%24335%2C000%20in%20March%202020%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.redfin.com%2Fcity%2F11458%2FFL%2FMiami%2Fhousing-market%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Redfin%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20rocked%20affordability%20in%20Miami%2C%20whe