%20reality.%20As%20I%20think%20about%20it%2C%20I%20keep%20coming%20back%20to%20one%20thing%3A%20impulse%20spending.%20I%20do%20this%20kind%20of%20spending%20while%20scrolling%20on%20social%20media%2C%20where%20the%20ads%20target%20me%20specifically.%20I%20hate%20to%20admit%20the%20number%20of%20times%20I%20have%20gone%20down%20a%20rabbit%20hole%20with%20these%20ads%20and%20ended%20up%20buying%20something%20I%20never%20knew%20I%20wanted%20and%20certainly%20didn't%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20example%20of%20this%20type%20of%20spending%20is%20heading%20to%20a%20big%20box%20store%20without%20a%20list%20of%20specific%20items%20I%20need%20to%20keep%20my%20household%20running.%20I%20find%20myself%20in%20these%20stores%20saying%20things%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20look%20how%20cute%20that%20kitchen%20towel%20set%20is!%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BThis%20t-shirt%20is%20on%20sale%20for%20%249.99!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20types%20of%20impulse%20spending%20that%20have%20cost%20me%20the%20most%20over%20the%20years%20are%20going%20to%20my%20favorite%20store's%20websites%20and%20%26quot%3Bbrowsing%26quot%3B%20their%20sales%20and%20going%20to%20%26quot%3Blook%26quot%3B%20at%20bookstores.%20How%20many%20jeans%20have%20I%20bought%20that%20I%20only%20wore%20once%3F%20How%20many%20books%20have%20I%20started%20that%20I%20never%20finished%3F%20How%20many%20dresses%20were%20only%20in%20style%20for%20a%20season%3F%20Too%20many%20to%20count%20is%20the%20truthful%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENow%2C%20I'm%20changing%20my%20spending%20habits%20for%20the%20better%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20I%20have%20put%20some%20safeguards%20to%20help%20me%20avoid%20this%20unnecessary%20type%20of%20spending.%20Now%2C%20I%20put%20items%20in%20my%20online%20shopping%20cart%20and%20wait%2024%20hours%20before%20checking%20out.%20There%20are%20times%20when%20the%20item%20is%20no%20longer%20available%20the%20next%20day%2C%20and%20at%20other%20times%2C%20I%20will%20change%20my%20mind%20about%20one%20or%20two%20things%20and%20remove%20them%20from%20the%20cart%20%E2%80%94%20but%20what%20happens%20most%20frequently%20is%20deciding%20to%20cancel%20the%20order%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20no%20longer%20go%20shopping%20at%20any%20store%20without%20a%20list.%20If%20I%20need%20to%20go%20to%20Costco%20or%20Target%2C%20I%20make%20a%20list%20just%20like%20I%20do%20for%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20and%20I%20stick%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20I%20have%20started%20following%20the%20actions%20of%20friends%20and%20family%20members%20who%20regularly%20use%20their%20library%20cards%20instead%20of%20purchasing%20books.%20I%20have%20many%20writer%20friends%2C%20and%20I%20will%20always%20buy%20their%20books%20to%20support%20them%2C%20but%20most%20of%20my%20book%20purchases%20don't%20fit%20in%20that%20category.%20If%20there%20is%20a%20new%20book%20I%20want%20to%20read%2C%20I%20can%20get%20on%20a%20waitlist%20and%20check%20it%20out%20digitally%20from%20my%20library.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20my%20husband%20won't%20be%20retiring%20in%20a%20few%20weeks%2C%20it's%20not%20too%20late%20to%20change%20course.%20I%20can't%20lie%20%E2%80%94%20I%20am%20disappointed%20that%20my%20husband%20can't%20turn%20in%20his%20ID%20badge%20and%20stay%20home%2C%20but%20seeing%20where%20we%20could%20have%20made%20a%20big%20difference%20in%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffinancial-plan%5C%22%3Efinancial%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20years%20isn't%20a%20bad%20thing.%20We%20won't%20be%20work-free%20this%20year%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20too%20late%20to%20save%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20and%20spend%20our%20last%20few%20years%20pre-retirement%20developing%20better%20habits%20that%20will%20help%20us%20build%20up%20our%20accounts%20now%20and%20help%20us%20when%20we%20do%20finally%20retire%20to%20live%20on%20a%20reduced%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20comes%20too%20late%20for%20early%20retirement%2C%20but%20not%20too%20late%20to%